# SEO Standards (CRITICAL)

This is a **public-facing marketing website**. SEO directly impacts lead generation. Every change must consider search engine impact.

---

## 1. Page Metadata

Every page MUST export metadata with at minimum `title` and `description`:

```tsx
import type { Metadata } from "next";

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "AI Scribe for Medical Practices | Mentera",
  description:
    "Automate clinical documentation with Mentera's AI Scribe. HIPAA compliant, real-time transcription for private practices.",
};
```

For dynamic pages (blog posts), use `generateMetadata()`:

```tsx
export async function generateMetadata({ params }: Props): Promise<Metadata> {
  const post = await blogService.getPostBySlug(params.slug);
  return {
    title: post?.title,
    description: post?.description,
    openGraph: {
      title: post?.title,
      description: post?.description,
      images: [post?.image],
    },
  };
}
```

### Metadata Checklist

- ✅ Title under 60 characters, includes primary keyword
- ✅ Description under 160 characters, compelling CTA
- ✅ OpenGraph title, description, and image
- ✅ Twitter card with `summary_large_image`
- ✅ Canonical URL (auto-generated via layout middleware)

---

## 2. Heading Structure

**Single `<h1>` per page. Strict hierarchy. No skipping levels.**

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<h1>AI Scribe for Medical Practices</h1>
  <h2>Key Features</h2>
    <h3>Real-time Transcription</h3>
    <h3>HIPAA Compliance</h3>
  <h2>Pricing</h2>

// ❌ Wrong — skipping h2
<h1>AI Scribe</h1>
  <h3>Features</h3>      // BAD: skipped h2!
```

### Rules

- Only ONE `<h1>` per page (enforced)
- `<h2>` for major page sections
- `<h3>` for subsections within an `<h2>`
- Use semantic HTML: `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`

---

## 3. Canonical URLs

The middleware (`src/middleware.ts`) injects `x-pathname` into headers, which the root layout uses to generate canonical URLs dynamically via `alternates.canonical`.

- **Never** hardcode canonical URLs in individual pages
- The root layout handles it automatically
- Base URL: `https://mentera.ai`

---

## 4. Structured Data (JSON-LD)

Root layout includes Organization, WebSite, and SoftwareApplication schema.

When adding new page types, add appropriate schema:

- **Blog posts** → `Article` or `BlogPosting` schema
- **Product pages** → `SoftwareApplication` or `Product` schema
- **FAQ sections** → `FAQPage` schema

```tsx
<script
  type="application/ld+json"
  dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{
    __html: JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      headline: post.title,
      datePublished: post.date,
      author: { "@type": "Person", name: post.author },
    }),
  }}
/>
```

---

## 5. Sitemap (`src/app/sitemap.ts`)

**Every public page must be in the sitemap.**

When adding a new page:

1. Add entry to `staticPages` array in `sitemap.ts`
2. Set appropriate `changeFrequency` and `priority`
3. Blog posts are auto-included from Contentful

### Priority Guide

| Page Type                               | Priority | Change Frequency |
| :-------------------------------------- | :------- | :--------------- |
| Homepage                                | 1.0      | weekly           |
| Product pages (AI Scribe, Integrations) | 0.9      | monthly          |
| Demo / Contact                          | 0.9      | monthly          |
| Blog listing                            | 0.9      | weekly           |
| Blog posts                              | 0.8      | monthly          |
| Legal pages                             | 0.5      | yearly           |

---

## 6. Robots

`src/app/robots.ts` controls crawler access:

- Allow: `/` (everything public)
- Disallow: `/api/`, `/admin/`
- Sitemap reference: `https://mentera.ai/sitemap.xml`

---

## 7. Images

- Always use `next/image` `<Image>` for automatic optimization, lazy loading, and responsive sizing
- Set `alt` text on every image (accessibility + SEO)
- Use `priority` prop for the first visible image (LCP optimization)
- OG image: `/og-image.png` (1200x630)
- Blog images: served from Contentful CDN or `/images/blog-medspa-*.jpg` placeholders

---

## 8. Core Web Vitals

| Metric                                  | Target  | How to Maintain                                                           |
| :-------------------------------------- | :------ | :------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **LCP** (Largest Contentful Paint)      | < 2.5s  | Optimize hero image, use `priority` prop                                  |
| **CLS** (Cumulative Layout Shift)       | < 0.1   | Set explicit `width`/`height` on images, avoid dynamic content above fold |
| **FID/INP** (Interaction to Next Paint) | < 200ms | Minimize client-side JS, defer non-critical scripts                       |

### Script Loading

- GTM: `strategy="afterInteractive"` (not blocking)
- GTM init (dataLayer): `strategy="beforeInteractive"` (required for tracking)
- Vercel Analytics: loaded as component (already optimized)

---

## 9. LLMs.txt

The site serves `/llms.txt` for AI model discoverability. Update this file when adding significant new content or product features.

---

## Anti-Patterns (SEO)

- ❌ Pages without `metadata` export
- ❌ Multiple `<h1>` tags on a page
- ❌ Skipping heading levels (h1 → h3)
- ❌ Missing `alt` text on images
- ❌ New pages not added to `sitemap.ts`
- ❌ Using `<img>` instead of `next/image`
- ❌ Blocking scripts loaded with `beforeInteractive` unnecessarily
- ❌ Content loaded client-side that should be server-rendered for indexability
